<HEADLINE>
<P>
'QUEEN' FOR A SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was glad to see a question about George Nader in Sunday's TV Times (Aug. 
21). I always felt he was underrated, but I must take exception to your 
statement, "Nader was the first 'Ellery Queen' in 1958."I am old enough to 
remember "Ellery Queen" with Lee Bowman (his best part, in my opinion) coming 
on live television as a summer replacement and later becoming a regular TV 
series. 
</P>
<P>
 John McCarthy, Culver City 
</P>
<P>
 Editor's Note: George Nader, in fact, played the third network "Ellery Queen" 
and the fourth overall. Richard Hart was first (Dumont, 1950-51); Lee Bowman, 
second (ABC, 1951-52); Hugh Marlowe, third (Syndicated, 1954); Nader, fourth 
(NBC, 1958-59); Lee Philips, fifth (NBC, 1959); and Jim Hutton, sixth (NBC, 
1975-76). 
</P>
</TEXT>
