<TEXT>
<P>
 RECKONING THE EARTH: Some Lessons From the Land by Sandra Murphy, illustrated 
John MacDonald (Northland Publishing: $12.95; 119 pp., paperback original). 
Long Branch Farm is a working agricultural installation designed as a showplace 
for children from nearby Cincinnati. Volunteer Sandra Murphy recalls how kids 
and their parents react to her talks about crop rotation, composting and farm 
animals, as well as the hands-on experiences of digging potatoes and making 
felt from raw wool. Her unpretentious essays leave the impression that she 
would make an engaging guide, providing the tour didn't involve too much time 
shoveling horse manure into the compost bins. 
</P>
