BEACH BLANKET BOOKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By E.W. Alexander 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 New this week:  
</P>
<P>
 JAMES HERRIOT'S CAT STORIES by James Herriot (St. Martin's Press: $16.95). 
Though retired, the North Yorkshire, England, veterinarian's 50 years of 
service continues to fill volumes. 
</P>
<P>
 IN LOVE WITH NORMA LOQUENDI by William Safire (Random House: $25) . Safire's 
mistress is his love of language. Here he dissects the everyman's voice, choice 
and meaning of words. 
</P>
<P>
 YOU ARE SPECIAL: Words of Wisdom from America's Most Beloved Neighbor by Fred 
Rogers (Viking: $18.95). For the past 25 years parents have shared a healthy 
cup of wisdom with Mr. Rogers in the mornings. His serene and practical counsel 
is now in book form. E.W. Alexander 
</P>
