<P>
 SMALL FACES: The pre-worldwide-fame days of the Red Hot Chili Peppers are 
being chronicled in "Out in L.A.," a collection of early recordings, including 
previously unreleased live and demo tracks and remixes. The EMI album is due in 
stores Oct. 4. . . . Annie Lennox is at work on her second post-Eurythmics 
album, due in early '95. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 Anita Baker is putting plans together for her first concert tour in four 
years, tentatively set to begin on the West Coast in December. . . . Look for 
the second album by female R&B trio SWV to be in stores in December. . . . 
Kirsty MacColl has recorded a duet with the Lemonheads' Evan Dando, which will 
be among the new tracks included on "Galore," a MacColl "best of" album due 
Oct. 18. . . . 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress Hill has finished four songs for its next album, due early next year, 
with a tour planned to follow. . . . The first live album from John Hiatt -- 
with the cheeky title "Hiatt Comes Alive at Budokan" -- is due in November, 
with one previously unreleased song among the 17 tracks. 
</P>
