<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHAT'S DEFENSE? GRAMBLING, ALCORN PUT ON SOME SHOW; TIGERS WIN, 62-56 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Grambling State's Kendrick Nord passed for 485 yards and seven touchdowns and 
Alcorn State's Steve McNair passed for 534 yards and five touchdowns as 
Grambling escaped with a 62-56 victory Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The two teams combined for 1,318 yards total offense.Grambling rolled up 612; 
Alcorn 706. 
</P>
<P>
 In an incredible offensive display, the two teams combined for 70 points in 
the first half, battling to a 35-35 standoff before a record Robinson Stadium 
crowd of 25,347. 
</P>
<P>
 McNair completed 27 of 52 passes and also rushed for 99 yards, giving him 633 
yards total offense, just 10 short of the Division I-AA record. McNair, who was 
3-0 against Grambling, had one final shot at rallying Alcorn, but his pass on 
fourth-and-10 from the Grambling 11 with four seconds left was knocked down by 
freshman Christopher Sampson in the end zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
