<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUHLER RUSHES FOR 248 YARDS, FIVE TOUCHDOWNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southern California Christian running back Ken Buhler rushed for 248 yards and 
five touchdowns in a 42-0 victory over Maui Kaahumanu Hou late Friday at Maui 
War Memorial Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Buhler, a senior running back, carried 12 times and scored on runs of 30, 12, 
8, 72 and 16 yards. His five rushing touchdowns were one short of the Orange 
County record shared by SCC graduate Mike Jacot, who did it in 1991 against 
Capistrano Valley Christian. Quarterback Steve Schinhofen scored the Flames' 
other touchdown on a one-yard run. 
</P>
<P>
 SCC (1-0) outgained Kaahumanu Hou (0-2) on the ground, 360 to minus-seven. Ron 
Wood rushed six times for 74 yards and Jeremy Smith had two carries for 48 
yards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
