<HEADLINE>
<P>
EDDIE MARTIN WILL BE REMEMBERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I'm afraid the item "Eddie Who?" (Newswatch, Aug. 29) may have left the 
wrong impression with many of your readers about the dedication of those of us 
at Martin Aviation to the memory of our founder, the late Eddie Martin. 
</P>
<P>
 No one, no group, and certainly no organization will be sadder to see the 
coming demise of the old Eddie Martin Terminal building than we.But we also 
recognize that the building is simply not capable of being restored for any 
kind of public use. Nor has there ever been any particular joy at Martin 
Aviation over the name change of Orange County Airport itself. However, it is 
not true that the only thing remaining in the memory of Eddie will be the 
display of Eddie Martin memorabilia at our headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
 Indeed, the name Martin Aviation by itself is a tribute to Eddie and his 
brothers Floyd and Johnny. As for the name of the new Martin Aviation 
headquarters, that will continue to be known as Martin Aviation. Forget Eddie 
Martin? We wouldn't -- and couldn't dream of it. 
</P>
<P>
 PATRICK J. KENNA 
</P>
<P>
 Vice President and General Manager 
</P>
<P>
 Martin Aviation 
</P>
