<TEXT>
<P>
 * According to Jerome Greenblatt (Letters, Aug. 28), all that females in the 
work force have to do to avoid the type of sexual harassment imposed upon Robyn 
Boyd during her employment on the staff of Assemblyman Mickey Conroy is to 
simply change jobs. Women should continue to do this until they find an 
environment free of types such as Mr. Conroy. 
</P>
<P>
 Greenblatt doesn't offer any estimate of how many job changes this might 
require. He is putting the responsibility of finding an acceptable work 
environment upon the female employee. This is exactly the attitude which 
foments sexual harassment. 
</P>
<P>
 No! Mr. Greenblatt, the responsibility is upon the employer and his 
administrative staff to create an environment free from grandfatherly, sexually 
sick individuals such as Mr. Conroy, who put up signs in their office stating 
that "sexual harassment will be graded" and who expect hugs and kisses from 
their female staff. 
</P>
<P>
 NORMA LONG 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 
</P>
