<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROSENTHAL AS SENATOR IS NOT FOREGONE CONCLUSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Thanks to Times reader M. Stephen Sheldon for exposing the Westside 
political machine that has been running the Valley for over two decades -- 
leading to a loss of jobs, rising crime, an influx of illegal immigrants and 
falling home prices. 
</P>
<P>
 Unfortunately Mr. Sheldon has concluded that Westside resident Herschel 
Rosenthal will become our next state senator and the plundering and 
mismanagement of the Valley will inevitably continue.Rosenthal's victory is not 
a foregone conclusion, and Valleyites should start looking at the candidates 
closely instead of voting a straight party line. Although mostly Democrats, the 
majority of Valley residents do not accept ultra-leftist Rosenthal's 
philosophy. He has advocated giving free syringes to drug addicts and other 
misuses of public resources. The Republican candidate, Delores White, who 
actually lives in the Valley, has a long record of facilitating economic growth 
-- not chasing it out of the state. 
</P>
<P>
 GREGG KAUFMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Reseda 
</P>
</TEXT>
