<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANOGA PARK WANTS TO KEEP TOPANGA PLAZA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * As a resident of the San Fernando Valley for 18 years, I am enthusiastic 
about Councilwoman Laura Chick's efforts to revitalize the central valley.My 
concern is the Topanga Plaza Shopping Center's efforts to associate itself with 
the Warner Center. 
</P>
<P>
 I feel Topanga Plaza's efforts to desert the community of Canoga Park are 
shameful and counterproductive to the revitalization process. Topanga Plaza is 
not now nor has it ever been a part of the Warner Center. It is a vital part of 
Canoga Park. 
</P>
<P>
 I hope community members and Councilwoman Chick's office will join in asking 
Topanga Plaza to change its signs and advertising from Warner Center to Topanga 
Plaza at Canoga Park. 
</P>
<P>
 LOUISE SCHILLACE 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge 
</P>
</TEXT>
