<HEADLINE>
<P>
BURBANK RESIDENTS CELEBRATE SUCCESSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * The voters of Burbank will continue to hold our community leaders 
accountable even without Sharon Woodson-Bryant's help. We will continue to 
participate in maintaining the positive values of a clean, safe, family 
oriented community.We are doing this with residents who take pride and 
responsibility in our churches, our schools and our politics. 
</P>
<P>
 It is Woodson-Bryant who missed the point of a diverse society. I did not 
celebrate Black History month this year and probably won't next year. 
</P>
<P>
 But I did celebrate with quiet pride a boy's graduation from high school this 
year. He is going to a major university with high academic standing and an 
athletic scholarship. I met him 10 years earlier. I don't know if he would have 
failed in another community, probably not. But I know he succeeded here in 
Burbank. He succeeded while getting all the bumps and bruises that life choose 
to give him. 
</P>
<P>
 R.A. MOSKUN 
</P>
<P>
 Burbank 
</P>
</TEXT>
