<TEXT>
<P>
 LIBRARY RETURN: When Eugene Wright of Perris recently lost his purse at the 
Santa Ana Library -- with $304 inside -- police gave him a 1% chance of ever 
seeing it again. But it showed up in his mail -- with $300, and a note from 
Mary V. Napolitano of Santa Ana. She wrote almost apologetically that she 
shorted him the $4 -- to cover postage to mail it back to him. . . . She said 
she grabbed the purse to keep someone else from stealing it. She declined his 
reward offer: "I didn't do it to get anything back." 
</P>
<P>
 SERRA FACE LIFT: Serra Chapel is California's oldest church and the only 
remaining structure in which Father Junipero Serra said Mass. . . . This month, 
work crews resume renovation of the 216-year-old chapel at Mission San Juan 
Capistrano. Gerald Miller, the mission administrator, said one of the chapel's 
features, adobe, has also been its bane. "Adobe structures are constantly 
absorbing moisture and deteriorating." Care will be taken, he said, to protect 
delicate wall motifs that are original drawings. 
</P>
<P>
 FAVORITE SON: Cypress is going to roll out a hometown welcome Thursday for one 
of its younger celebrities, Tiger Woods. . . . Woods, 18, recently became the 
youngest ever to win the U.S. Amateur Golf Championship. The city is holding a 
free, open-to-everyone reception for him. Said Councilwoman Joyce C. Nicholson: 
"He is just a wonderful young man. It's a pleasure to have him as a resident." 
Reception is from 5:30 to 8 p.m. at the Cypress Golf Club. 
</P>
<P>
 CANYON HANDS: Activists against development of Laguna Canyon are planning a 
midday concert next Saturday on Laguna Canyon Road to drum up public support 
for preservation of the rugged area. . . . Michael Phillips, a spokesman for 
the Laguna Canyon Conservancy, said the Hands Along the Canyon event will run 
from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. and will include state Sen. Tom Hayden (D-Santa Monica) 
and actor David Clennon, who played Miles Drentell on the TV show 
"thirtysomething." 
</P>
