<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARSON SUSPECTED IN TARZANA FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fire that caused more than $100,000 damage to a blue jeans company Saturday 
was intentionally set, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fifty firefighters responded to the blaze at K.C. Jeans, in the 18000 block of 
Topham Street, at 5:47 a.m, said Jim Wells of the Los Angeles City Fire 
Department. The fire was put out a little more than an hour later. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no injuries, Wells said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire officials would not say why they believed the fire was the result of 
arson. There are no suspects in the blaze, Wells said. 
</P>
<P>
 The one-story building sustained $100,000 in structural damage and $15,000 in 
damage to its contents, Wells said. 
</P>
